diagnosis.final_diagnosis: thoracic lipomeningocele associated with diastematomyelia, tethered spinal cord, and hydrocephalus
diagnosis.diagnostic_reasoning: The diagnosis was supported by spinal MR imaging revealing multiple spinal malformations, including diastematomyelia and a thoracic lipomeningocele, as well as the presence of a dermoid cyst, syringomyelia, and moderate supratentorial ventricular dilation.
